This paper proposes an unsupervised disparity fusion method using adversarial networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which could potentially place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the paper deals with stereo vision, which could place it in the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
